<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 21 at 4:02PM CDT until July 21 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Little Rock has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Clark County in southwestern Arkansas...
North central Pike County in southwestern Arkansas...
Southeastern Montgomery County in western Arkansas...
* Until 445 PM CDT.
* At 359 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Glenwood, or
12 miles southeast of Mount Ida, and is nearly stationary.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Glenwood...                       Welsh...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
